body_html:
@AndreyRub Yes, the whl file you reference seems to only be the TF Python API which wraps around a precompiled native library for Windows.

The process for Android is a bit different; please refer to https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/tree/master/tensorflow/examples/android which contains basic instructions for running the demo with Bazel. If it doesn't work on Windows you could probably build it in a VM, or wait for the cmake support that will be coming soon.
